## Preservation requirements
- Do NOT change unrelated existing behavior.
- Existing tests must continue to pass after your edits.
- Match the project's existing style and structure -- do not refactor
  the codebase to your preferences.
- Do not delete files unless the change explicitly requires it.

## Verification
- Read enough of the existing code to understand the change before
  editing. Use the Read tool, not assumptions.
- Run the existing test suite BEFORE making changes (record the
  baseline counts via `mcp__kenning_coding__report_test_results`).
- Run it again AFTER making changes; both runs must come back clean.

## Testing requirements for new code
- Any new behavior gets new tests, in the project's existing test
  framework and style.
- Run the full test suite after writing new tests; all green before
  declaring complete.

## Reporting + clarification
- Use `mcp__kenning_coding__report_progress` after each meaningful
  unit of work; include files touched.
- Use `mcp__kenning_coding__request_clarification` if the change
  requires substantive input (scope, credentials, paid services,
  breaking choices). For implementation details, use sensible defaults
  consistent with the existing code.
- Use `urgency: "blocking"` when you cannot proceed; `"preference"`
  when you have a default.
